Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telegram from Khieu Samphan to King Norodom Sihanouk </F>
voicing support for the royal statement dated 7 March -- read by 
announcer] 
  [Text] To His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, king of 
the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  Your Majesty: I and all members of the Party of Democratic 
Kampuchea [PDK] have received with great pleasure your majesty's 
statement dated 7 March 1994. 
  The PDK has the great honor and pleasure to voice its full 
support for the content of the statement. The PDK is convinced 
that our entire nation and people will certainly march behind 
Your Majesty so that you will be able to fulfill your five-point 
guideline. Please forgive any inappropriateness. [Dated] 8 
March 1994 [Signed] Khieu Samphan, head of the PDK 

